<main id="main" role="main" class="infinite recipe" data-post-type="articles">
    <div class="holder">
        <div id="content" class="article">
            

            <article class="news-post">
    
    
    <ul class="breadcrumbs">
<li>
<a href="/category/recipes/">Recipes</a> </li>
<li>
<a href="/category/dish-type/">Dish Type</a> </li>
<li>
<a href="/category/soup-and-stew-recipes/">Soup and Stew Recipes</a> </li>
</ul>
                <div class="news-article">
                <h1 class="title-gallery" data-post-id="2149776" id="title-gallery" data-author="Michelle McGlinn" data-category="soup-and-stew-recipes" data-content_type="Recipe" data-mod_date="2026-04-18" data-layout="Infinite" data-post_id="2149776" data-pub_date="2026-04-18" data-day="Saturday" data-dayhour="Saturday-7AM" data-pubhour="7AM" data-num_slides="17" data-num_words="1000" data-pitcher="Kate Shuey" data-trello_board="Recipes" data-intent="evergreen" data-ideation="trendbot">Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe</h1>
            </div>

    
                <div class="news-article">
                
                                <div class="byline-container">
                    <div class="byline-text-wrap">
                        <span class="byline-by">By</span> <a href="/author/michellemcglinn/" class="byline-author">Michelle McGlinn</a>
                         <span>and</span> <a href="/author/foodrepublicstaff/" class="byline-author">Food Republic Staff</a>
                        <span class="byline-timestamp">
                            <time datetime="2026-04-18T11:32:00+00:00">April 18, 2026 7:32 am EST</time></span>
                        
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap lead-image-holder" data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="0" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="paea0935b5981ea795d4d959d62e51efd">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/intro-1775745727.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/intro-1775745727.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/intro-1775745727.jpg" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="0" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: " width="780" height="438" alt="Ladling Italian wedding soup out of pot">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                
                        <div class="raptive-video-player"></div>
                <p dir="ltr">Right behind chicken noodle and classic, hearty tomato, Italian wedding soup is one of the first soups I remember loving as a kid. The itty bitty meatballs combined with tangy broth, silky greens, and tiny, tender pasta was culinary perfection in my eyes, and became my most frequent request during my family's weekly visits to the local Italian deli. At the time, I envisioned it as the soup Italians surely served at large, romantic weddings, thinking it must be a tradition to serve before the reception's main course. Like many, I was misled by the name, as the soup actually has nothing to do with weddings at all. </p>
<p>While the soup does have origins in Italy, the original version looked a little different than what we know and love today. <a href="https://www.foodrepublic.com/1652176/italian-wedding-soup-name-origin/" target="_blank">Originally called minestra maritata, or married soup</a>, the dish was simply named for its combination (or marriage) of rustic ingredients. It also didn't include the famous tiny meatballs, which would have been considered too expensive at the time. The wedding soup as we know it today is distinctly Italian-American, but that doesn't make it any less great. Still one of my favorite soups today, I developed an easy recipe for making it from scratch with fresh spinach, salty Parmesan, acini de pepe, and yes –- tiny, beefy meatballs, which flavor the soup with a marriage of savory flavor.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">The ingredients needed to make the best Italian wedding soup</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="1" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="pc3a38bc935020f4232ea2650665faa69">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/the-ingredients-needed-to-make-the-best-italian-wedding-soup-1775745728.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/the-ingredients-needed-to-make-the-best-italian-wedding-soup-1775745728.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/the-ingredients-needed-to-make-the-best-italian-wedding-soup-1775745728.jpg" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="1" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: The ingredients needed to make the best Italian wedding soup" width="780" height="438" alt="ingredients on a table">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>To make the meatballs, you'll need ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, an egg, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, and olive oil for searing. Save the rind of the Parmesan to use for the broth, which you'll be combining with onion, carrot, celery, garlic, Italian seasonings, chicken broth, and baby spinach. Lastly, seek out acini de pepe, which is a particularly small pasta that resembles quinoa or millet and is usually found near the orzo in the pasta aisle.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 1: Soak breadcrumbs in milk</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="2" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="p5f1bf83017df1272eecb4b20cf1361ab">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-1-soak-breadcrumbs-in-milk-1775745729.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-1-soak-breadcrumbs-in-milk-1775745729.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-1-soak-breadcrumbs-in-milk-1775745729.jpg" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="2" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 1: Soak breadcrumbs in milk" width="780" height="438" alt="breadcrumbs and milk mixed in a bowl">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Begin the meatballs: Combine the milk and breadcrumbs in a bowl. Let the milk soak into the breadcrumbs until the crumbs are paste-like, about 5 minutes.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 2: Mix the meatball ingredients</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="3" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="pb188fe11a8a9ad6b991249669d6f9ce2">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-2-mix-the-meatball-ingredients-1775745729.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-2-mix-the-meatball-ingredients-1775745729.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-2-mix-the-meatball-ingredients-1775745729.jpg" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="3" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 2: Mix the meatball ingredients" width="780" height="438" alt="meatball ingredients mixed in a bowl">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Add all meatball ingredients but the oil to the bowl. Use your hands to mix until just combined, being careful not to overmix.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 3: Roll out the meatballs</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="4" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="p19d3faad4d9d9fbf4ced5a269080974a">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-3-roll-out-the-meatballs-1775745730.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-3-roll-out-the-meatballs-1775745730.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-3-roll-out-the-meatballs-1775745730.jpg" loading="lazy" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="4" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 3: Roll out the meatballs" width="780" height="438" alt="rolling meat into meatballs">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Roll the mixture into ¾-inch meatballs, placing them on a parchment-lined baking sheet as you go.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 4: Heat oil in a pot</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="5" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="pbe2d1aa0a71c679c5fe7a7fa8104737f">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-4-heat-oil-in-a-pot-1775745730.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-4-heat-oil-in-a-pot-1775745730.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-4-heat-oil-in-a-pot-1775745730.jpg" loading="lazy" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="5" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 4: Heat oil in a pot" width="780" height="438" alt="oil heating in a pot">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Heat the 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 5: Sear meatballs</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="6" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="p8a1db93d3c8164517fd617f31192a04b">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-5-sear-meatballs-1775745731.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-5-sear-meatballs-1775745731.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-5-sear-meatballs-1775745731.jpg" loading="lazy" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="6" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 5: Sear meatballs" width="780" height="438" alt="searing meatballs in a pot">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Add the meatballs and sear on each side until browned, about 5 minutes total, working in batches as needed. (Note: The meatballs will not be cooked all the way through.)</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 6: Remove meatballs and add the vegetables</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="7" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="p3b45f7296f760fe98aca6d8a7dbf6101">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-6-remove-meatballs-and-add-the-vegetables-1775745731.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-6-remove-meatballs-and-add-the-vegetables-1775745731.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-6-remove-meatballs-and-add-the-vegetables-1775745731.jpg" loading="lazy" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="7" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 6: Remove meatballs and add the vegetables" width="780" height="438" alt="cooking vegetables in a pot">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Remove the meatballs from the pot and add the onion, carrot, and celery. Cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and stir.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 7: Add the broth and seasonings</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="8" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="pb115af74931d03d44e6d56e7a001cea1">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-7-add-the-broth-and-seasonings-1775745731.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-7-add-the-broth-and-seasonings-1775745731.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-7-add-the-broth-and-seasonings-1775745731.jpg" loading="lazy" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="8" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 7: Add the broth and seasonings" width="780" height="438" alt="broth and seasonings added to a pot">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Add the Italian seasoning, Parmesan rind, salt, pepper, and chicken broth to the pot. Return the meatballs to the pot.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 8: Boil the pasta</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="9" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="pa14ba9c7f2a08bea201c989111adbfc1">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-8-boil-the-pasta-1775745732.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-8-boil-the-pasta-1775745732.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-8-boil-the-pasta-1775745732.jpg" loading="lazy" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="9" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 8: Boil the pasta" width="780" height="438" alt="boiling pasta in pot">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Bring the soup to a boil, then add the acini de pepe and stir. Boil until meatballs are cooked through and pasta is al dente, about 10 minutes.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class="news-article">
                
                <h2 class="">Step 9: Wilt the spinach</h2>
                                <div class="slide-key image-holder gallery-image-holder credit-image-wrap " data-post-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe" data-slide-num="10" data-post-id="2149776">
                         
                                             <picture id="pe7cac0feef0f92b3b6bfee452e9d159e">
                                                    <source media="(min-width: 429px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-9-wilt-the-spinach-1775745732.webp" type="image/webp">
                            <source media="(max-width: 428px)" srcset="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-9-wilt-the-spinach-1775745732.sm.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img class="gallery-image " src="https://www.foodrepublic.com/img/gallery/our-best-italian-wedding-soup-recipe/step-9-wilt-the-spinach-1775745732.jpg" loading="lazy" data-slide-url="https://www.foodrepublic.com/2149776/italian-wedding-soup-recipe/" data-post-id="2149776" data-slide-num="10" data-slide-title="Our Best Italian Wedding Soup Recipe: Step 9: Wilt the spinach" width="780" height="438" alt="cooking spinach in a pot">
                    </source></source></picture>
                    <span class="gallery-image-credit">Michelle McGlinn/Food Republic</span>
                    </div>
				            <div class="columns-holder ">
                <p>Remove the Parmesan rind and add the spinach. Stir until spinach is wilted and bright green, about 1 minute.</p>

            </div>
